description:
## What

Bake the §14.8 default values into the actual Rust config struct (`crates/miroir-core/src/config/`) and the Helm `charts/miroir/values.yaml`. The plan asserts these defaults fit the 2 vCPU / 3.75 GB envelope; if the code defaults drift from the plan, the envelope claim becomes a lie.

Knobs from §14.8 (lines 3613-3672):

```yaml
miroir:
  server:               { max_body_bytes: 100 MiB, max_concurrent_requests: 500, request_timeout_ms: 30000 }
  connection_pool_per_node: { max_idle: 32, max_total: 128, idle_timeout_s: 60 }
  task_registry:        { cache_size: 10000, redis_pool_max: 50 }
  idempotency:          { max_cached_keys: 1_000_000 (~100 MB), ttl_seconds: 86400 }
  session_pinning:      { max_sessions: 100_000 (~50 MB) }
  query_coalescing:     { max_subscribers: 1000, max_pending_queries: 10000 }
  anti_entropy:         { max_read_concurrency: 2, fingerprint_batch_size: 1000 }
  resharding:           { backfill_concurrency: 4, backfill_batch_size: 1000 }
  peer_discovery:       { service_name: "miroir-headless", refresh_interval_s: 15 }
  leader_election:      { enabled (auto when replicas>1), lease_ttl_s: 10, renew_interval_s: 3 }
```

Plus K8s pod requests/limits: `cpu 500m / 2000m`, `memory 1Gi / 3584Mi` (3.5 GiB; leaves headroom under 3.75 GB).

## Why

`miroir-qon.5` (config struct) is closed but predates §14. Several of the §13.x features that consume these knobs were beaded later. Some defaults likely already match (validate); others may be missing or misaligned. Without them, `miroir_memory_pressure` (§14.9) will fire spuriously and the §14.7 sizing matrix becomes unverifiable.

## Acceptance

- [ ] Each §14.8 key present in `crates/miroir-core/src/config/` with the documented default
- [ ] `charts/miroir/values.yaml` exposes the same keys with identical defaults
- [ ] `values.schema.json` accepts the documented ranges; rejects nonsense (e.g., `lease_ttl_s < renew_interval_s`)
- [ ] K8s resources block in `templates/miroir-deployment.yaml` matches §14.8 (500m/2000m CPU, 1Gi/3584Mi mem)
- [ ] Unit test: serializing the default Config struct produces a YAML equal to the §14.8 listing modulo formatting
- [ ] Drift guard: a doc-test or CI step compares `Config::default()` against the §14.8 reference YAML

Parent epic: `miroir-m9q` (Phase 6 — Horizontal Scaling). Cross-cuts: `miroir-qjt.2` (Helm values), `miroir-qjt.3` (values.schema.json).

## What

Implement the `values.schema.json` constraints called out across the plan:

1. **`miroir.replicas > 1` requires `taskStore.backend: redis`** (plan §6, §14.4)
2. **`hpa.enabled: true` requires `replicas >= 2 AND taskStore.backend: redis`** (plan §14.4)
3. **`search_ui.rate_limit.backend: local` rejected when `miroir.replicas > 1`** (plan §13.21 + §14.6)
4. **Admin login rate-limit `backend: local` rejected when `miroir.replicas > 1`** (plan §4 `admin_sessions` / §13.19)
5. **`search_ui.scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days >= scoped_key_max_age_days`** (plan §13.21 "Config validation")
6. Any other "Helm schema rejects..." callouts found across the plan

## Why

Plan §13.21 Config validation paragraph is explicit: "such a configuration would cause rotation to fire immediately (or before) key issuance, producing a continuous rotation loop." These schema checks catch class-of-error misconfigurations at `helm install` time rather than at 3 AM.

## Details

Use JSON Schema `if/then` and `not`:
```jsonc
{
  "$id": "https://github.com/jedarden/miroir/charts/miroir/values.schema.json",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "miroir": { ... },
    "taskStore": { ... },
    "search_ui": { ... }
  },
  "allOf": [
    { "if": {...replicas>1...}, "then": {...backend==redis...} },
    { "if": {...hpa.enabled...}, "then": {...replicas>=2 AND backend==redis...} },
    {
      "if": {...replicas>1...},
      "then": {...search_ui.rate_limit.backend !== "local"...}
    },
    {
      "properties": {
        "search_ui": {
          "properties": {
            "scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1},
            "scoped_key_max_age_days": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 2}
          },
          "allOf": [
            {
              "not": {
                "properties": {
                  "scoped_key_rotate_before_expiry_days": {...},
                  "scoped_key_max_age_days": {...}
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Test cases** (in `charts/miroir/tests/`):
- Each constraint has a `bad-values.yaml` that must fail `helm lint --strict`
- A `good-values.yaml` that must pass

**Error messages**: use `errorMessage` extension where operator-readable matters (e.g., "SQLite task store cannot run with multiple replicas; set taskStore.backend=redis").

## Acceptance

- [ ] 5+ bad-values.yaml files all fail `helm lint --strict` with clear messages
- [ ] good-values.yaml combinations pass
- [ ] Phase 9 CI includes the schema rejection tests
